I agree with 'tony'. It's good for 'CAM' quality but that's about it. Can't see the dark scenes and if you wear headphones or have a stereo system, the left side quit in and out the WHOLE time...If you don't mind missing the 'environment' (the creepy factor) of a movie, and have your a/v system set on mono, you might like this one.
